<strong>What is Linkpager.com?</strong><a name="WhatIs"></a>
<p><a href="http://www.Linkpager.com" title="Linkpager">Linkpager.com</a> is a place where you can store your favorite places on the internet your way. With a free account, you can create folders and lists to store and organize your bookmarks online.</p>
<a href="#top">top</a> <hr />
<br />
<strong>How does it work?</strong><a name="HowDoes"></a>
<img src="Images/Screens/linkpager_console.jpg" alt="Linkpager: Bookmarking Console" width="350" style="float:right; margin:5px" />
<p>With you login with your free account, you are taken to your home screen where you can name and add Folders, as well as Lists within those Folders. When you create it a List, it is placed in whatever Folder you are currently in. By default, newly created Lists are placed in the HOME or unsorted Folder.</p>
<p>Once you have created a new List by giving it a name and a description (optional), you can then click on that list to edit it.</p>
<p>You add a link by clicking [ADD LINK] on the right, and then pasting the URL (Internet Address) in the textbox that appears. After clicking the button, LINKPAGER will go out and grab the site Name and Description to save you some typing. You can, of course, change that to whatever you wish.</p>
<p>Links can also be edited to change their name, description, and private/public status. Private links are not displayed to anyone except the author.</p>

<p>By clicking PREVIEW from the home screen, you can see what a List looks like when shared, and even reshare via <a href="http://www.facebook.com" title="Facebook" target="_blank">Facebook</a>, 
<a href="http://www.twitter.com"title="Twitter" target="_blank">Twitter</a>, and many more options.</p>
<p>For more detailed instructions, please visit our <a href="StepByStep.aspx" title="Step By Step">Step by Step instructions</a>.</p>

<a href="#top">top</a> <hr />
<br />
<strong>How much does it cost?</strong><a name="HowMuch"></a>
<p>It is <u>FREE</u> to create an account on LINKPAGER and start collecting and organizing your favorite places. Lists are supported with ads (but not tacky eyesores), so feel free to live free.</p>
<a href="#top">top</a> <hr />
<br />
<strong>How do I access my favorites?</strong><a name="AccessFave"></a>
<p>You can register and sign in to LINKPAGER.com with either your LINKPAGER or Facebook account through Facebook Connect.</p>
<p>Any browser will do (<a href="http://windows.microsoft.com/en-US/internet-explorer/products/ie-9/home?os=win7&arch=b&browser=ie" title="Internet Explorer" target="_blank">IE</a>, 
<a href="http://www.apple.com/safari/" title="Safari" target="_blank">Safari</a>,
<a href="http://www.google.com/chrome" title="Google Chrome" target="_blank">Chrome</a>,
<a href="http://www.firefox.com" title="Mozilla Firefox" target="_blank">Firefox</a>, etc.) from your desktop, laptop, netbook, tablet, or web enabled mobile device. You can bring your favorite places with you wherever you go without worry.</p>
<a href="#top">top</a> <hr />
<br />
<strong>What is a Folder?</strong><a name="WhatFolder"></a>
<p>You create and name a Folder to organize your Lists.</p>
<a href="#top">top</a> <hr />
<br />
<strong>What is a Linkpage?</strong><a name="WhatList"></a>
<p>You create and name a Linkpage in a Folder (It goes in your HOME Folder by default). You then add Links to your Linkpage to help keep them organized in whatever manner you choose.</p>
<p>A Linkpage has a name as well as a description to help you detail what is contained in the list.</p>
<a href="#top">top</a> <hr />
<br />
<strong>Can I share a Linkpage?</strong><a name="ShareList"></a>
<p>What good is organizing all of your favorite places unless you can easily share the whole list? Linkpager lets you share your Lists with whomever you choose through several sharing options.</p>
<a href="#top">top</a> <hr />
<br />
